Confluence allows you to set the interval at which it "Synchronizes" between LDAP and Confluence, but does not include this option for any Crowd/JIRA directories.

Workaround:
You can manually add this into the db by discovering the directory id (query the cwd_directory table) and then:

{code}
confdb=# insert into cwd_directory_attribute (directory_id, attribute_value, attribute_name) values (DirID ,TimeInSeconds,'directory.cache.synchronise.interval');


{code}

Filling in DirID with the directory id, and the TimeInSeconds the interval.

