If you create a page with the following wiki markup, none of the lines renders as monospaced text:

{noformat}
{{ foobar}}
{{foobar }}
{{ foobar }}
{{foo}}bar
foo{{bar}}
{noformat}

This prevents you using monospace text in some circumstances.

*Workaround*

In the latter two cases, any kind of punctuation will enable the monospace to work. For example:

{noformat}
abso-{{techno}}-lutely
{{enum}}'s
{noformat}

Both the above cases will render the monospace text correctly in recent versions of Confluence.

When adding images in the rich text editor between 2 lines of text for example, when you save the page, the image is placed side by side within text when it should be between them.

Confirmed in versions 3.5 and 3.4.

Example: Wikimarkup:
{code}
testtesttesttesttesttesttesttest

!image_name.jpg|border=1!

testtesttesttesttesttesttesttesttest
{code}
Will become after saving:
{code}
testtesttesttesttesttesttesttest !image_name.jpg|border=1!
testtesttesttesttesttesttesttesttest
{code}

