Currently, neither LDAP nor Crowd provide the option to use SASL when connecting to Active Directory using a privileged bind DN.  This is a request to add support for SASL for connections to Active Directory.

There is a similar request for Crowd (CWD-1812), this is a request to bring the same functionality to Confluence via embedded Crowd.

{code:java}
public URI getDocumentationBaseUrl()
{
    return URI.create("http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/APPLINKS");
}
{code}

Instead (since according to Sarah M all the AppLinks pages are included in the Confluence documentation space) this should dynamically return the base URL of the docs.atlassian.com redirect target, e.g. 

{noformat}
http://docs.atlassian.com/confluence/docs-035/
{noformat}

I've made this 'Critical' as all AppLinks docs urls will be incorrect until this work is done, and it should be a lightning quick change.

